      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="X32-10M1" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">By Dr. <hi rend="underline">SHERIDAN</hi>.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">D</hi>EAR Dean, since you in sleepy wise</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-line-2"> Have op'd your Mouth, and clos'd your Eyes,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-line-3"> Like Ghost I glide along your Floor,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-line-4"> And softly shut the Parlour Door;</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-line-5"> For should I break your sweet Repose,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-line-6"> Who knows what Money you might lose?</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-line-7"> Since oftentimes it has been found,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-line-8"> A Dream has giv'n ten thousand Pound.</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-line-9"> Then sleep, my Friend, dear Dean, sleep on,</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-line-10"> And all you get shall be your own.</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-line-11"> Provided you to this agree,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-X32-10M1-line-12"> That all you lose belongs to me.X32-10M1   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
